text: The Papyrus Deissmann (P.Coll Horsley, P.Horsley, LDAB 3095, TM 61938, vHTR 30a, Rahlfs 865) is a septuagint manuscript written in papyrus that contains parts of the Book of Exodus. By comparative writing styles (palaeography), it has been dated to 3rd-century. Currently is kept at Armidale, Private collection, Australia. == References == == Sources == * * * Category:Septuagint manuscripts Category:3rd-century biblical manuscripts
